0.1 Packages

import Pkg; Pkg.add("PGFPlotsX")
using Plots, PGFPlotsX, LaTeXStrings

1 pgfplotsx backend

Uses Plots syntax with pgfplotsx backend engine.

1.1 Polynomial function

# normal plot(x,y)

pgfplotsx()
x1 = range(-2,2,length=50)
y1 = x1.^3
plot(x1,y1, framestyle=:origin, leg=false, 
     size=(300,250),lw=2,linecolor=:black)

1.2 Recipe: scatter

# recipe scatter(x,y)

x2 = [2,3,3.5,4,4.5,5]
y2 = [3.5,5,4,6,4.5,5.5]
scatter(x2,y2, leg=false, size=(400,300), framestyle=:origin)
scatter!([0,4],[0,5], color="red",markersize=5)
scatter!([4],[3],color="yellow", ms=6)

1.3 Recipe: surface

default(size=(400,300),
        fc=:heat,
        xlabel="x",
        ylabel="y",
        zlabel="z",
        )
surface(-4:1:4,
        -5:1:5,
         (x,y)-> -x/6+y/2,
         )

1.4 Recipe: surface

surface(range(-3,3, length=30), 
        range(-3,3, length=30),
        (x, y) -> x^2-y^2,
        label=L"x^2-y^2",
        colormap_name = "viridis",
        size=(400,300),
        colorbar=false)
pgfplotsx
